external_knowledge:
- "Garden" refers to the educational environment;
- "Flowers" refer to the courses;
- "Gardeners" refer to the students;
- "Seeds planted" refer to the registration dates;
- "Caretakers" refer to the instructors;
- "Water" refers to the total cost of the course registrations;
- "Type of flower" refers to the course name;
- "Name of the gardener" refers to the student name.

- "blossoms of knowledge" refers to courses;
- "bees" refers to students;
- "buzzing around" refers to student registrations;
- "more than one bee" refers to a count of student registrations greater than 1.

- `categories` table represents different garden plots;
- `courses` table represents the seeds planted in each plot;
- `cost` represents the cost of planting the seeds.

- The term "students" refers to the individuals who have registered for courses;
- "Signed up" implies that there is a record of their registration in the `registrations` table;
- "Courses that have instructors and schedules" means courses that are linked to an instructor and have a schedule defined in the `course_schedules` table.

- 'blossomed' refers to courses that have at least one registration;
- 'gardeners' refers to instructors;
- 'bees' refers to registrations;
- 'nectar' refers to the payment amount.

- "blossoms" refers to courses;
- "nurturers" refers to instructors;
- "bees" refers to students;
- "nectar" refers to the amount paid for course registrations.

- "plants" refer to students;
- "types of soil" refer to courses;
- "how the garden is tended" refers to the format of the courses (e.g., online, on-campus).

- "Blooming courses" refers to courses with the highest number of registrations;
- "Blossoms" represent the total number of registrations for a course;
- "Ripe fruits" represent the number of confirmed registrations;
- "Financial yield" represents the total revenue generated from confirmed registrations;
- "Scheduled seasons" refer to the number of schedules, earliest start date, and latest end date for a course;
- "Categories" and "formats" refer to the specific types of courses (e.g., online, on-campus).

- 'Total revenue' is the sum of all payments made for the registrations of a course;
- 'Number of students' refers to the count of unique student IDs registered for a course;
- 'Average number of students' is the mean number of students across all courses taught by an instructor.

- "Instructors" refers to the individuals teaching the courses;
- "Students" refers to the individuals who have registered for the courses;
- "Average course cost" is the mean cost of all courses taught by an instructor;
- "More than 5 students" means the total number of registrations for courses taught by an instructor is greater than 5.

- "Blooming in the garden of learning" refers to the courses being offered in the educational system;
- "Tended by their respective instructors" refers to the instructors assigned to each course;
- "Scheduled in various time slots" refers to the different schedules for each course;
- "With or without students enrolled" refers to the possibility of courses having registered students or not.

- 'Online courses' are courses that are delivered through the internet, allowing students to participate remotely.;
- 'More than 10 students' implies a threshold of 11 or more students.;
- 'Popular' in this context refers to the number of registrations, with higher numbers indicating more popularity.

- "leading lights" refers to the most popular instructors;
- "shine the brightest" refers to having the highest number of student registrations;
- "top 3 courses" refers to the courses with the highest number of registrations.

- "running total" refers to a cumulative sum that increases with each new registration payment;
- "drops of water filling a bucket" is a metaphor for the accumulation of payments over multiple registrations;
- "flow" refers to the order in which the payments are accumulated and reported.

- 'Garden' refers to the category of courses;
- 'Flower blooming' refers to the courses within a category;
- 'Cumulative revenue' is the running total of revenue as each course (flower) is added to the category (garden).

- "Planted their seeds in courses" refers to students who have registered for courses;
- "Courses that have yet to bloom" refers to courses that have not started yet;
- "Wise gardeners (instructors)" refers to the instructors of the courses;
- "Fellow learners joining them" refers to the number of students registered for each course.
